BACK IN THE DAY, PEOPLE THAT WORKED AS CUSTODIANS LIVED IN THE BUILDINGS WHERE THEY WORKED.
FOR RONALD CLARK, WHO'S DAD WAS THE CUSTODIAN OF THE LIBRARY, MEANT THAT HE ACTUALLY GREW UP AND LIVED IN THE LIBRARY.
HE WAS TELLING THIS STORY TO HIS DAUGHTER, JAMLIAH.
HE SAID THAT HIS DAD WASN'T JUST THE CUSTODIAN, HE WAS THE KEEPER OF THE TEMPLE OF KNOWLEDGE.
AND HE LIVED IN THE TEMPLE OF KNOWLEDGE.
HE GREW UP THINKING THEY WERE RICH, BUT THEY WEREN'T, HE JUST DIDN'T HAVE ANYTHING YET TO COMPARE IT TO.
HE REMAINED QUIET IN THE LIBRARY DURING THE DAY, BUT ONCE IT CLOSED, HE COULD RUN AROUND AND PLAY.
HE NEVER BROUGHT ANY FRIENDS OVER BECAUSE HE WAS SORT OF ASHAMED AT FIRST.
HE READ AND READ AND WHEN HE COULDN'T SLEEP AT NIGHT, HE'D GO DOWN AND READ SOME MORE.
HE GREW UP TO BECOME A PROFESSOR AND SHOWED HIS DAD HIS CLASSROOM, WITH HIS NAME ON THE DOOR "PROFESSOR CLARK".
HIS DAD DIDN'T SAY MUCH, BUT HE WAS PROUD.
HIS DAD HAD ALWAYS WANTED HIS SON TO ASPIRE TO BE MORE THAN WHAT HE HAD.
NO ONE IN HIS FAMILY HAD YET GONE TO COLLEGE, HE WAS THE FIRST ONE TO GO AND GRADUATE.
HE IS VERY GRATEFUL TO HAVE LIVED IN THE LIBRARY AND WONDERS HOW DIFFERENT HIS LIFE WOULD HAVE BEEN IF HE HAD NOT LIVED IN THE LIBRARY.
PROFESSOR CLARK GREW UP IN THE LIBRARY.
HIS DAD WAS THE CUSTODIAN THERE AND BACK THEN, THE CUSTODIANS LIVED IN THE BUILDINGS THEY CARED FOR.
SO RONALD AND HIS PARENTS LIVED IN THE LIBRARY.
HIS DAD WOULD WAX ALL OVER, INCLUDING THE TOPS OF THE BOOKSHELVES.
WHEN HE COULDN'T SLEEP, HE COULD STAY UP TIL 3AM READING.
HE NEVER BROUGHT ANY FRIENDS OVER BECAUSE HE WAS ASHAMED WHEN HE WAS YOUNGER.
BUT HE WAS REALLY GRATEFUL BECAUSE HE GOT TO READ A LOT.
HE GREW UP THINKING HIS FAMILY WAS RICH.
HE HAD TO BE QUIET DURING THE DAY BUT COULD BE LOUD AND RUN AROUND THE LIBRARY AT NIGHT ONCE IT WAS CLOSED.
HE WAS THE FIRST IN HIS FAMILY TO GO TO COLLEGE AND HE BECAME A PROFESSOR.
HE SHOWED HIS DAD HIS CLASSROOM AND THE DOOR THAT SAID "PROFESSOR CLARK" AND HIS DAD DIDN'T REALLY SAY ANYTHING.
HE WAS TELLING THIS STORY TO HIS DAUGHTER.
